2015-06-04 14:58:09	-->	x1337807x (~x1337807x@208.100.138.243) has joined ##linux
2015-06-04 14:58:11	ayecee	the details of how.. what details?
2015-06-04 14:58:35	ayecee	the find program takes the argument of -exec and replaces any instance of {} with the filename for each invocation of the arguments.
2015-06-04 14:58:38	cjohnson	when using it with -exec, it will take all of the following commands (up to \;) and run them, replacing {} with the filename
2015-06-04 14:59:06	-->	kerneloopz (~kerneloop@unaffiliated/kerneloopz) has joined ##linux
2015-06-04 14:59:13	cjohnson	find . -exec echo {} \;   would basically do the exact same thing as find .
