2015-06-09 13:47:22	GNU\colossus	San1ty, it replaces your shell's proces (image) with another. after you `exec some_other_program` in sh, whatever your shell was "planning" to do after that exec, is without consequence.
2015-06-09 13:47:25	<--	notebox (~textual@cbs1-lewi17-2-0-cust4.2-4.cable.virginm.net) has quit (Quit: My Mac has gone to sleep. ZZZzzz…)
2015-06-09 13:47:39	alankila	GNU original guidelines were to write utilities without arbitray limitations, both as to avoid claims of copying (limitless algorithms are quite different from limited ones in many places), and to be better than traditional unix
2015-06-09 13:47:42	-->	LauraCottontail (uid62174@gateway/web/irccloud.com/x-tdbrkdsunojtzwnj) has joined ##linux
