2015-06-09 13:49:09	FreezingDroid	oh, I needed single quotes.
2015-06-09 13:49:11	bls	San1ty: so you have a shell/shell script, every command that shell executes becomes a child of that shell, and those children can have their own childer. when you know you're not going to be executing anything else, you can "reparent" all those (5yo) children to the final command via exec. this means that controlling that final command also allows you to controll all the previously created children
2015-06-09 13:49:27	-->	gnostikoi_ (~user@c-67-180-2-131.hsd1.ca.comcast.net) has joined ##linux
